	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The wiki page for the DMC says that when the sample buffer is empty, that "The CPU is suspend for up to four clock cycles." So if I have a timed loop after a sprite0 hit like so...
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx #2<br />_loop:&nbsp; &nbsp;nop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;nop&nbsp; &nbsp;; &lt;-- buffer is empty here on the first iteration<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;nop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;dex<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;bne _loop<br /></div>
<br />
<br />...will the rest of the loop be delayed for four cycles (or more, if it becomes empty again)?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


