	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can always write your code so that being off by 12 pixels won't matter.</div>
<br />HBlank has 85 pixels, so depending on what you want to do, the extra delay won't matter at all. For changing the scroll, for example, only the last couple PPU writes must actually fall inside HBlank, so there's quite a lot of wiggling room. Changing the palette, however, needs more HBlank time.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
